body:
Hello,
verilator errors out when parsing `foreach` after an implication in constraints.

A simplified code showing this is:

```
class ahb_transaction;

  typedef enum logic [2:0] {
    AHB_SIZE_8,
    AHB_SIZE_16,
    AHB_SIZE_32,
    AHB_SIZE_64,
    AHB_SIZE_128,
    AHB_SIZE_256,
    AHB_SIZE_512,
    AHB_SIZE_1024
  }             size_t;

  // Address
  rand logic [31:0]              haddr[];

  // Size
  rand size_t                    hsize;

  // Address aligment
  constraint haddr_align_c {
    hsize == AHB_SIZE_16   ->  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][0]   == 0;
    hsize == AHB_SIZE_32   ->  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][1:0] == 0;
    hsize == AHB_SIZE_64   ->  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][2:0] == 0;
    hsize == AHB_SIZE_128  ->  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][3:0] == 0;
    hsize == AHB_SIZE_256  ->  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][4:0] == 0;
    hsize == AHB_SIZE_512  ->  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][5:0] == 0;
    hsize == AHB_SIZE_1024 ->  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][6:0] == 0;
  }

endclass;
```

When I try to run it, I get:

```
%Error: ahb_master_transaction.sv:22:32: syntax error, unexpected foreach, expecting IDENTIFIER-for-type
   22 |     hsize == AHB_SIZE_16   -&gt;  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][0]   == 0;
      |                                ^~~~~~~
        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html?v=5.042 for more assistance.
%Error: ahb_master_transaction.sv:23:32: syntax error, unexpected foreach, expecting IDENTIFIER-for-type
   23 |     hsize == AHB_SIZE_32   -&gt;  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][1:0] == 0;
      |                                ^~~~~~~
%Error: ahb_master_transaction.sv:24:32: syntax error, unexpected foreach, expecting IDENTIFIER-for-type
   24 |     hsize == AHB_SIZE_64   -&gt;  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][2:0] == 0;
      |                                ^~~~~~~
%Error: ahb_master_transaction.sv:25:32: syntax error, unexpected foreach, expecting IDENTIFIER-for-type
   25 |     hsize == AHB_SIZE_128  -&gt;  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][3:0] == 0;
      |                                ^~~~~~~
%Error: ahb_master_transaction.sv:26:32: syntax error, unexpected foreach, expecting IDENTIFIER-for-type
   26 |     hsize == AHB_SIZE_256  -&gt;  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][4:0] == 0;
      |                                ^~~~~~~
%Error: ahb_master_transaction.sv:27:32: syntax error, unexpected foreach, expecting IDENTIFIER-for-type
   27 |     hsize == AHB_SIZE_512  -&gt;  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][5:0] == 0;
      |                                ^~~~~~~
%Error: ahb_master_transaction.sv:28:32: syntax error, unexpected foreach, expecting IDENTIFIER-for-type
   28 |     hsize == AHB_SIZE_1024 -&gt;  foreach(haddr[i])  haddr[i][6:0] == 0;
      |                                ^~~~~~~
%Error: Exiting due to 7 error(s)</pre>
```

What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?

```
verilator --cc ahb_master_transaction.sv
```

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?  Did you try it with other simulators?

```
Verilator 5.042 2025-11-02 rev v5.042
```

I did not try the latest GIT master version, but since `5.042` I have not found any commits that would
deal with such topic.

The code works in VCS without problems.

I did not see much sense in forming the test_regress format since the verilator does not even pass
the compilation here. If you would like me to prepare the test in the test_regress format, please let
me know.

What OS and distribution are you using?

```
Linux runner4.tropic.dev.hq.sldev.cz 4.18.0-553.58.1.el8_10.x86_64 #1 SMP Thu Jun 12 14:27:07 EDT 2025 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux
```

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?

Yes, that would be appreciated.

